{
  "texts": [
    "Here, an Enhanced Curvelet Transform (ECT) technique was applied to denoise the signal by excluding the irrelevant positions and noisy contents.",
    "Sequentially, the quantitative information from the preprocessed signal was extracted by applying the graph and texture-based feature extraction mechanism.",
    "Then, the Grey Level Co-occurrence Matrix (GLCM) technique was deployed to extract the statistical information for simplifying the process of abnormality detection.",
    "Finally, the Random Forest (RF) classification technique uses the selected feature vectors to label the signal as normal or abnormal.",
    "Tsiouris et al."
  ]
}